On Mon, 7 Jan 2002, jeremy norris wrote:

I have had a similar problem for years and finally figured it out.  I
takes over 15 minutes of interstate driving to recharge a single engine
start.   throw in accessories and it slowly brings a battery down.

 I live in a city and make a bunch of short trips so at least once a week
I put my batteries on an overnight trickle charge (automatic shut off)

seems to solve the problem.

other solution, longer trips, bigger batteries, bigger alternator.

this type of service is also hard on batteries and shortens their life
markedly.

